Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.34,0:00:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The most crucial moment in life is during decision making.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.30,0:00:14.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The Pacific War taught us the preciousness of peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.41,0:00:20.49,Default,,0,0,0,,But also instilled \Nnumerous lessons on how to live.{unsure, lit is "for the sake of living, precepts, numerous left behind"}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.87,0:00:31.88,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fade(100,700)\c&H0007DF&\fs100\b1\bord0\blur1}Animentary\N{\b\c&HE0DBF3&}Decision
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.56,0:00:43.48,Default,,0,0,30,,Wit is your weapon{honestly no clue what is megurase here, deepl says "rack one's brain"}\NRemember to use your head{智恵をめぐらせ 頭を使え}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.48,0:00:51.45,Default,,0,0,30,,Repress your anguish, \NIf you are a man{悩み抜け抜け 男なら}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.45,0:00:59.74,Default,,0,0,30,,One decision is enough \NTo make others cry or laugh{泣くも笑うも 決断ひとつ}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.74,0:01:07.19,Default,,0,0,30,,If you win, don't hold your head high, \NIf you lose, don't cry{勝っておごるな 敗れて泣くな}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.19,0:01:15.05,Default,,0,0,30,,Men, don't you ever let others see your tears{男 涙は見せぬもの}
Comment: 0,0:01:35.41,0:01:35.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{ch}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.50,0:01:50.06,Default,,0,0,0,,December 2nd, 1941.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.06,0:01:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Six days before the surprise attack at Pearl Harbor.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.57,0:01:57.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The great fortress of Singapore, \Nthe Britain's pride, is in exceedingly high spirits. {to get excited; to be in an uproar}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.89,0:02:04.95,Default,,0,0,0,,That day, brand new ships arrive to the port \Nto bolster the British East Indies fleet - Z-Force. {https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Force_Z} {new species; new variety}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.95,0:02:07.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Comprised by a battleship Prince of Wales
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.33,0:02:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and a battlecruiser Repulse, \Nit stands prepared to protect the colony. {added}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.80,0:02:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,This transfer has been announced worldwide,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.38,0:02:19.26,Default,,0,0,0,,creating an unquestionable appearance \Nof Singapore's defenses being impregnable. {impregnable; invulnerable; unassailable; cast-iron} {lit: nobody would doubt the belief that ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.26,0:02:25.18,Sign,,0,0,300,,{\c&HF2F1EA&\b1\bord0\blur1}Episode 7 \N {\fs80} High Seas Naval Battle for Malaya
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.04,0:02:29.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Prince of Wales -
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.52,0:02:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,formerly deployed in the Atlantic,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.51,0:02:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,she stood her ground \Nagainst the German battleship Bismark. {lit is " did not yield; to give in; to be daunted; to shrink/succumb to the bismark's attack" but bismark never hit her so idk what to make of it, it's more of a testimony to her luck than to her endurance: Prince of Wales continued to exchange fire with Bismarck but suffered serious malfunctions in her main armament. The British battleship had only been completed in late March 1941, and used new quadruple gun turrets that were unreliable. Prince of Wales soon broke off the engagement.[1]}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.73,0:02:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,With the cutting-edge technology on-board, her fame of an unsinkable battleship was was roaring across the globe. {to make (one's name, etc.) widely known}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.96,0:02:46.27,Default,,0,0,0,,35,000 tons. Cruising speed of 28.5 knots.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.27,0:02:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Armed with ten 35 cm cannons,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.27,0:02:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,as well as sixteen 13 cm high-angle guns. {techinally "anti-aircraft " works too but it'll be used in the next line separately}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.78,0:02:56.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Also on-board, mounted co-axially 8 pieces per turret \Nand dubbed "pom-pom,"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.73,0:02:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,anti-aircraft guns with firing rate of 6000 per minute,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.93,0:03:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Aside from that, numerous dual machine guns {/mounted coaxially in 2}\Nare mounted all over her.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.76,0:03:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Battlecruiser Repulse.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.35,0:03:11.35,Default,,0,0,0,,32,000 tons, max speed 30 knots.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.35,0:03:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Though formally outdated{over 20 years older than PoW}, recently refitted \Nwith newest equipment like that on Prince of Wales. {lit is "hardly any change from PoW" and idk waht he means}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.47,0:03:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Meanwhile, at the Japanese military base \Non the Hainan Island. {trusting HA although kainan can be many things}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.07,0:03:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Admiral,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.38,0:03:28.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Prince of Wales and Repulse are at anchor in Singapore.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.35,0:03:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,If we sortie now, they will definitely come out. {unsure maybe he means "if they sortie"}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.62,0:03:33.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Surprise is our goal. \NMaking the landing a surprise is our priority.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.61,0:03:38.87,Default,,0,0,0,,However, with those still around, attempting a landing under the enemy's radar involves much more risks. {no fucking clue what he means: while doing without being seen (by); to do behind (someone's) back; to do without the knowledge of (e.g. one's parents)​ the enemy, definitely reach/make it to the landing point there is no guarantee - would assume he advocates wiping out Z-Force now, saying "if we don't and try to just pass in sneakily, there's no telling if we won't be intercepted"}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.87,0:03:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. With the British East Indies Fleet still in the area, \Nthe Army supply through the sea is jeopardized.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.30,0:03:46.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The British fleet needs to be eliminated \Nas soon as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.46,0:03:48.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Commander,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.61,0:03:53.13,Default,,0,0,0,,please let our air squadron \Nshow Prince of Wales and Repulse their place! {repulse; repelling (e.g. the enemy); driving back}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.13,0:03:54.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Good. Please do.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.62,0:03:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,If need be, I'm prepared to even sacrifice \Nthe entirety of our escort fleet,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.52,0:04:00.14,Default,,0,0,0,,in order to get our landing party \Nsafely to the destination.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.14,0:04:01.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.24,0:04:03.97,Default,,0,0,0,,We won't let them lay a finger on our convoys!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.97,0:04:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,A certain death from the sky awaits them if they come out.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.77,0:04:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,"The sun rises at Yamagata" -
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.40,0:04:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,such a coded{unsure it's the right word, it's actually "a telegram, carrying a code"} telegram meant that the onset of the war \Nwas scheduled on December 8th.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.16,0:04:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,On receiving that cue, the Japanese troops set out
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.51,0:04:27.79,Default,,0,0,0,,on their furtive advance through the Malay Peninsula \Nwith Singapore as their ultimate goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.72,0:04:30.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Dead ahead and above! {unsure what he means: sky; the skies; high-altitude sky; upper air forward; frontward; ahead​}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.27,0:04:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,British plane, one vehicle!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.80,0:04:39.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So they finally decided to stick their head out!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.80,0:04:40.93,Default,,0,0,0,,No two ways about it:
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.93,0:04:46.16,Default,,0,0,0,,the enemy must be radioing Singapore with "Found \Na large Japanese formation" like mad right about now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.16,0:04:49.31,Default,,0,0,0,,If the British East Indies Fleet sorties now, we'll be in deep. {/comes out}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.31,0:04:52.81,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you talking about? \NShould even the Prince of Wales come out now,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.81,0:04:57.79,Default,,0,0,0,,the seas west of the Anambas Archipelago \Nare already bristling with our mines.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.73,0:05:03.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And even if they try to trick us, coming from the East, {unsure what he means by "by mistake/otherwise"}\Nthey'll just end up in the tight snare of our submarine fleet. {lit: get caught in the network of ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.05,0:05:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,However,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.02,0:05:08.62,Default,,0,0,0,,if the British realize \Nthe intent behind our surprise landing, {by the way, I have no clue what's he talking about}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.62,0:05:11.08,Default,,0,0,0,,it will spell trouble for the entire Malayan campaign. {/will be hindered}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.00,0:05:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll be alright.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.12,0:05:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,As per our plan, we'll make a false report on our course,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.63,0:05:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,misrepresenting it as bound for Thailand. {/making it look}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.44,0:05:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{Roger!}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.11,0:05:26.54,Default,,0,0,0,,A big Japanese formation is advancing towards Bangkok.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.54,0:05:31.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The composition: 25 transport ships, one battleship, \N5 cruisers, 7 destroyers.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.80,0:05:34.94,Default,,0,0,0,,However,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.94,0:05:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,in Singapore, the overall commander of the British \NEast Indies forces, Air Chief Marshal Brooke-Popham {Most notably, Brooke-Popham was Commander-in-Chief of the British Far East Command until being replaced a few weeks before Singapore fell to Japanese troops. - we've seen in eps 4-6 that the overall commander was Percival, maybe we should include a note here that percival was only appointed to this position shortly after the invasion?}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.63,0:05:47.43,Default,,0,0,0,,still in doubts about the true intentions of the Japanese convoys, failed to enact any countermeasures.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.18,0:05:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,As a result, the Japanese transports \Nsuddenly changed course to the west at 00:45 on the 8th
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.39,0:05:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and began landing on parts \Nof the Malay Peninsula, completely unopposed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.10,0:06:03.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Upon receiving reports of this, Phillips, \Nthe Commander-in-Chief of the British East Indies Fleet
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.47,0:06:05.47,Default,,0,0,0,,gathered his closest staff.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.47,0:06:10.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The Japanese troops that finished landing last night \Ncan only have this one thing in their sights - Singapore.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.48,0:06:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The Japanese realize that a frontal attack from the sea \Nwould not suffice to bring down a fortress like Singapore.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.75,0:06:21.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It falls on us, the pride of the British fleet{added}, the Z-Force,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.59,0:06:25.09,Default,,0,0,0,,to launch a surprise attack, under the Air Force coverage,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.99,0:06:27.62,Default,,0,0,0,,blowing the Japanese out of the water. {lit: to destroy japanese fleet}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.62,0:06:30.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The Japanese battleships are traveling \Nwith the escort of 20 warships. {unsure what he means, why would battleships need escort, I'd rather belive them being escorts for convoys, lit is "japanese army battleships covering escorting warships - 20 vessels"}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.91,0:06:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And we made it known to the whole world \Nthat Prince of Wales and Repulse are now in Singapore.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.92,0:06:39.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Now is not the time for us to hesitate.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.04,0:06:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,When we meet the enemy, \Nwe face him decisively, hitting hard. {unsure what he means by "hit that/blow/shoot that"}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.43,0:06:49.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Such has been the lifelong tradition of our Royal Navy, \Nand our article of pride!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.43,0:06:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,At 5:35 pm of the 8th,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.20,0:06:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,with Prince of Wales as its flagship, \NZ-Force of the British East Indies Fleet
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.22,0:07:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,had set sail from Singapore's naval base \Nso as to deal a surprise blow to Japanese convoys.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.85,0:07:23.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir, a telegraph from the Air Force Command.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.21,0:07:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Fighters on bases heavily damaged by Japanese bombardment.{trying to keep this concise as the telegrams go} Cannot provide cover for Z-Force.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.20,0:07:31.74,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.74,0:07:36.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, the surprise attack is possible without air coverage. \NPass the Anambas{ Archipelago} from the east and proceed to the north! {unsure how to word it, he says "make a hook/curve around ..."}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.02,0:07:42.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The Japanese also know that passing them \Nfrom the west would be the shortest route. {if we pass them, we do it from the west}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.62,0:07:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So they made it impassable with mines.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.49,0:07:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Knowing that waters west of Anambas Archipelago \Nare swarming with mines, the Z-Force
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.83,0:07:53.95,Default,,0,0,0,,manages to bypass them safely and head north.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.83,0:07:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,However, next afternoon, on the 9th,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.50,0:08:01.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the Z-force was still entirely oblivious to the fact
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.18,0:08:04.05,Default,,0,0,0,,a fleet of Japanese submarines was patrolling this route.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.90,0:08:06.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The report of the Z-Force being spotted
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.97,0:08:11.01,Default,,0,0,0,,was promptly radioed \Nto the base of the 22nd Japanese Air Flotilla.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.63,0:08:32.20,Default,,0,0,0,,5th Submarine Fleet, 30th Submersible Squadron{lit is just "30th submersible/submarine" but I'd assume they have multiple layers of units in submarines and idk how to really reflect it in EN; https://ja.wikipedia.org/wiki/%E4%BC%8A%E5%8F%B7%E7%AC%AC%E7%99%BE%E5%85%AD%E5%8D%81%E4%BA%94%E6%BD%9C%E6%B0%B4%E8%89%A6}, \Nan emergency radiogram from I-65.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.20,0:08:32.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Read it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.92,0:08:35.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Spotted: 2 enemy's Repulse-class battlecruisers.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.49,0:08:36.47,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.47,0:08:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Read.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.20,0:08:38.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Observed from the east.{guess, really. not in HA's script either, shiten may be "point of view; viewpoint; angle; perspective" or at least a solstitial point, but kochisa - no clue at all, but kochi may be east wind; spring wind so eh... whatever}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.36,0:08:41.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Course at 340 degrees. Speed at 14 knots. 1515. {this last number must be time - 15:15, may write it like that for clarification}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.81,0:08:42.89,Default,,0,0,0,,That's nonsense!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.48,0:08:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean by that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.48,0:08:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Prince of Wales and Repulse were seen still in Singapore
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.69,0:08:50.79,Default,,0,0,0,,by our reconnaissance plane just this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.99,0:08:53.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So who should we believe here?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.92,0:08:57.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Order the reconnaissance photos printed. It's urgent. {development (of film); photographic processing}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.17,0:09:11.14,Default,,0,0,0,,This is just a large merchant ship. {no clue what's this oowata, believing HA}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.14,0:09:13.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It's neither Prince of Wales nor Repulse.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.70,0:09:17.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Which means, the ones spotted by I-65...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.89,0:09:19.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Are the real ones! {/the radiogram from I-65... is true!}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.25,0:09:20.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The enemy is heading our way.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.39,0:09:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright. Sortie! {/attack}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.60,0:09:36.97,Default,,0,0,0,,At 5:34 pm, {I-65's amplifying report, confirming the presence of British battleships, reached 22nd Air Flotilla headquarters two hours later. At that time, their aircraft were in the process of loading bombs for an attack on Singapore Harbour, but they immediately switched to torpedoes. The bombers were not ready until 1800 hours.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.97,0:09:39.64,Default,,0,0,0,,from the air base in Saigon, Indochina {no clue what this tsudoomu, was "and Tudomo" in HA's, but there's no city of such name anywhere, only Tsudome but it's in Sapporo; this word's placements suggest some status or proper name like "official/usual" or "Saigon Zudomo air base" but again, can't find any clues, only "the Dorm hotel" in Saigon; repeated in line at 11:31 as tsudoomu but still no clue what it is again, would translate as "in Indochina" for consistency if we ever figure this out}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.64,0:09:43.62,Default,,0,0,0,,a wing of torpedo bombers took off, \Ntasked with attempting a raid on the Z-Force.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.74,0:10:06.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The Japanese convoys east of the Malay Peninsula \Nimmediately retreated to safety of Thai coastal waters.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.22,0:10:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,With heavy cruiser Chokai as its core{actually he just says "starting the HC chokai, ..." and idk what he means, maybe "starting with?"}, the escort fleet
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.92,0:10:14.93,Default,,0,0,0,,sets out, determined to destroy Britain's Z-Force, \Nin cooperation with the Air Force fleet. {advance; charge}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.93,0:10:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll join the pantheon of heroes \Nby sinking Prince of Wales. {no clue what he means, lit is "if we daiuchi PoW, no regrets" - no clue what's this daiuchi either, may be "big hit/major damage" but why'd he say no regrets? he doesn't have anything to regret as it is now, unless he means "if we go down on the hands of pow, I regret nothing" but that's unthinkably defeatist thing to say, assumed he means "our mission is only justified if we do ... to pow"}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.60,0:10:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,We must, by all means, stop them from getting close, \Nuntil all our troops are disembarked!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.90,0:10:29.08,Default,,0,0,0,,By all means!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.76,0:11:21.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Ain't nothing we can do in this storm.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.05,0:11:23.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Should we retreat?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.39,0:11:30.05,Default,,0,0,0,,8:10 pm.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.52,0:11:36.43,Default,,0,0,0,,the torpedo bombers that took off from the Indochina bases \Ndiscovered a fleet that looked like what might be Z-Force. {this tsudoumu again, still no clue, still replacing with indochina}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.40,0:11:45.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Found enemy ships. Course at{guess, no clue what's this ohitonyu; not in HA's either} 150 degrees, 140 km.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.94,0:11:54.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Those halfwits! {scatterbrain; absent-minded person; careless person; thoughtless person}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.53,0:11:56.53,Default,,0,0,0,,They mistook us for the enemy fleet.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.53,0:11:58.95,Default,,0,0,0,,If we don't respond {to the signal }promptly, \Nwe'll be under attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.42,0:12:02.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Radio this out immediately:\NFlare dropped over our allied fleet. {/got illuminated}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.46,0:12:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Weather over the ocean is deteriorating.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.28,0:12:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Scouting is impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.50,0:12:13.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We've already had one case \Nof friendly ships being mistaken for the enemy. {/made a mistake}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.56,0:12:15.80,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.80,0:12:17.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Withdraw the attack wings.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.90,0:12:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll face them tomorrow! {lit: match/fight/confrontation is ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.24,0:12:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,In turn, the British fleet
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.74,0:12:26.45,Default,,0,0,0,,convinced that the Japanese scout aircraft \Nhad discovered them, was rapidly turning back.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.08,0:12:28.09,Default,,0,0,0,,However,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.09,0:12:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,the Japanese side never really discovered Z-Force.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.12,0:12:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Thus,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.33,0:12:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,however miraculous, \Nboth the enemy and the friendly forces {strangely; oddly; miraculously; mysteriously}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.96,0:12:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,turned their backs at one another \Nand parted ways at the same moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.94,0:12:59.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Having abandoned the prospect of a surprise attack, Z-Force \Nwas on its way back to Singapore.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.32,0:13:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Until, at 00:52 on the 10th...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.23,0:13:12.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir, we've got an emergency call \Nfrom the headquarters in Singapore.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.04,0:13:14.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The report says, the Japanese troops \Nare attempting a landing in Kuantan.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.22,0:13:15.87,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.87,0:13:17.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir, a surprise attack is possible!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.54,0:13:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,We're 640 km away from the Japanese air base in Saigon. {At 1:45 am, the British fleet turned 180 degrees and Vice Admiral Phillips decided to attack the Japanese convoy off Kuantan.}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.21,0:13:24.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The threat from the Japanese planes is negligible. {lit is "first, getting attacked by ... don't worry" I'd assume he means "we don't have to worry about being attacked first, thus giving them initiative, because we're outside of their operational range (this was a common belief in royal navy at the time)" tho unsure, having to cram this tightly due to cps}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.41,0:13:27.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Both the enemy convoys and the escort vessels \Nare currently ours for the taking! {lit: we are able to smash both ... and ... at the same time}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.91,0:13:30.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright. This time, we don't sidestep. {lit: we do it this time}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.45,0:13:32.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Send one destroyer ahead for scouting.{actually just "let one ... go ahead/first"}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.93,0:13:39.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Z-Force sent out the destroyer Express \Nto Kuantan as a liaison.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.14,0:13:43.43,Default,,0,0,0,,With hopes of dealing a surprise blow to the Japanese fleet \Nglowing in them, the Z-Force set out on its way. {/begin advancing}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.86,0:13:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,However,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.24,0:13:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,once again, Z-Force was entirely oblivious
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.34,0:13:53.43,Default,,0,0,0,,to the presence of a Japanese submarine I-58, \Nshadowing their every move. {At 1:22 a.m. on December 10, submarine I-58 (submarine commander Soshichi Kitamura), which was watching the movement of the British fleet in the same area, spotted the shadow of a destroyer-like ship at a close distance of 600 meters to the right of 20 degrees while navigating on the water. }
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.02,0:13:56.01,Default,,0,0,0,,We're not letting them get away this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.01,0:13:58.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep tracking the enemy until the very end.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.03,0:14:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Once we find them, \Nunleash a full-scale attack with all forces.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.86,0:14:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,"Unsinkable battleship" is but a legend.{no clue wha'ts this nogisurumonozo, may be "nani suru" but still no clue what it means, maybe if only in the sense "it may be 10 times a ..."} We can do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.22,0:14:06.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Sink Prince of Wales and Repulse with planes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.47,0:14:09.34,Default,,0,0,0,,This should definitely be doable!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.34,0:14:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Dispatch the recon aircraft at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.91,0:14:14.14,Default,,0,0,0,,4:55 am, December 10th{added}.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.14,0:14:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Nine Mitsubishi G3M land-based aircraft \Ntook off for a reconnaissance mission from Saigon air base. {At 6:25 on December 10, Maj. Gen. Matsunaga threw nine Type 96 land-attack aircraft (company commander, Captain Makino) of the 4th Motoyama Sky Company on a search mission .}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.81,0:14:34.74,Default,,0,0,0,,However, the Japanese efforts at locating \NBritish Z-Force were proving more and more futile. {to stray from the right path; to go wrong; to go off the rails; to turn delinquent}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.10,0:14:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,We've been here for five hours already.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.25,0:14:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.60,0:14:43.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Where did the Royal Navy go?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.54,0:14:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain, the planned 600 nautical miles mark was passed. {how exactly do you call a plane captain/pilot?}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.36,0:14:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.34,0:14:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You expect us to return empty-handed?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.80,0:14:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll keep searching until we find them. {to the very end; to the last; thoroughly; completely; fully​}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.42,0:14:51.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.47,0:14:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I can see the Malay Peninsula.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.22,0:14:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It's Kuantan.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.25,0:15:04.15,Default,,0,0,0,,At that moment, a dim shadow flashed through spotter's eyes. {lit is "shadow to be reflected; to harmonize with (harmonise); to come out (photo); to be projected; to be displayed (on a screen) in captain (of an aircraft)'s eyes" but I've no clue, would assume it means "caught attention/eye"; also translating it as "spotter" bc not everyone can be a captain, right? we clearly saw the other one being called this way and this guy is not even a pilot either}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.15,0:15:05.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, look!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.32,0:15:07.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Enemy ships!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.39,0:15:08.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Good, let's make sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.82,0:15:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Approach under the cover of clouds.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.32,0:15:10.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.25,0:15:23.07,Default,,0,0,0,,No room for mistake! It's Prince of Wales and Repulse!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.07,0:15:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,We did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.26,0:15:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Nice! Congratulations!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.73,0:15:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Operator{no clue what's this ruishin really is, could also be military rank, or proper name or whatnot}, a telegram!{/write this}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.06,0:15:28.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.34,0:15:32.18,Default,,0,0,0,,"Found Prince of Wales.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.18,0:15:36.39,Default,,0,0,0,,North latitude: 4 degrees. East longitude: \N3 degrees 55 minutes. Course: 60 degrees.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.64,0:15:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,They're giving us a warm welcome. {/shooting at us}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.34,0:15:46.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn! If only we had a torpedo with us!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.06,0:15:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Reconnaissance missions are a bore! {/boring}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.61,0:15:48.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.53,0:15:50.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't wage war all by yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.86,0:15:53.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Reconnaissance and {enemy ships }sinking missions \Nare equally important! {actually "are the same mission" but I'd assume he means this}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.53,0:15:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.77,0:15:57.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright. Keep an eye on them \Nuntil our attack planes arrive.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.41,0:16:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Ain't letting them get away!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.36,0:16:06.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Third recon{naissance} aircraft spotted the enemy{'s main forces} \Noff the coast of Kuantan.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.28,0:16:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't let them escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.36,0:16:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,We must make sure to sink them with planes!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.78,0:16:13.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Every attack wing is rushing to the coast of Kuantan.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.39,0:16:15.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish you a good fight! {this was in episode 1 or just in one of early episodes, lit is "I pray for your good fight" - 健闘祈る}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.59,0:16:32.14,Default,,0,0,0,,We should definitely expect the Japanese air attack. {/attack planes will come}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.14,0:16:35.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Prince of Wales fears not \Nany possible attack from above.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.91,0:16:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The enemy is unrelenting. {desperate - not sure which word to use in english, I think he means to say "stops at nothing"}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.03,0:16:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Our defensive plan must be impeccable. {lit: we must prepare the counterattacking measures to be perfect}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.64,0:16:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We would be fine, no matter when the attack comes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.98,0:16:43.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It's time to make a display \Nof the Royal Navy's stoicism. {bravery; heroism; gallantry}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.43,0:16:46.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Every single one enemy plane \Nmust be shot down into the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.91,0:16:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Enemy main forces are maneuvering. \NCourse: 60 degrees. Speed: 20 knots.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.96,0:17:03.29,Default,,0,0,0,,What's taking the attacking wings so long? {/slacking off/loiter around}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.29,0:17:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,They'd better be here soon!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.35,0:17:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.90,0:17:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no more fuel.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.53,0:17:13.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright. Everyone, jettison your things!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.97,0:17:15.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{Huh?}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.47,0:17:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll help save fuel.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.18,0:17:19.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Your weapons. Throw your clothes out, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.14,0:17:20.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.63,0:17:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,That was when eight planes of the Japanese air squadron \Ntook position 3,000 meters above Repulse.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.06,0:17:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,For the first time in the history of naval warfare, \Nthe airplane-on{/vs}-warship{/battleship} battle had begun.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.73,0:18:02.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Confirming a bomb hitting Repulse!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.97,0:18:04.73,Default,,0,0,0,,But it won't sink from just one.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.33,0:18:06.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Torpedo bombers are here!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.30,0:18:40.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Two torpedoes! Confirming hits on Prince of Wales!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.85,0:18:47.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The propulsion system stopped working! {ceasing (movement, activity, etc.); suspension (of operations); interruption (e.g. of electricity supply); cutting off}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.86,0:18:48.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.62,0:18:52.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Pound away at them! {to fire (a gun) ceaselessly; to fire away; to blaze away; to fire volley after volley} \NFight until the very last man!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.76,0:19:18.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Telegram to Singapore:
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.86,0:19:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,"Under heavy bombardment by the Japanese planes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.95,0:19:25.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The British are also hitting back pretty hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.10,0:19:27.33,Default,,0,0,0,,They're not giving up \Non their "unsinkable battleship!" {/as expected}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.85,0:19:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,8 planes of the 8th squadron,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.62,0:19:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,counting on you!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.17,0:19:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Torpedo squadron! \NThis time, counting on you for sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.90,0:20:20.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The British fleet was fighting back \Nwith tremendous tenacity. {tremendous; terrific; enormous; prodigious; stupendous; amazing}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.68,0:20:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.07,0:20:25.45,Default,,0,0,0,,It was Repulse, who met her end first.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.43,0:20:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Life jackets on! {trusting HA's "Put on your life jackets!" here, but really no clue, kyuumen must be "lifesaving" and yoi may be prepare, like in "prepare for evacuation/to be saved"}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.00,0:20:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Life jackets on!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.67,0:20:35.48,Default,,0,0,0,,All crew{no clue what's first word, trusting HA} gather on the upper deck. \NPrepare to abandon the ship. {leaving a warship; abandoning ship}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.40,0:20:37.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Lord help us all.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.49,0:21:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Repulse is sinking!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.84,0:21:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Glorious sight{rippana?}. She fought well.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.26,0:21:09.71,Default,,0,0,0,,As the battle progressed, Prince of Wales as well...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.26,0:21:11.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.51,0:21:12.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Pound them away!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.16,0:21:33.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.92,0:21:39.54,Default,,0,0,0,,All crew, abandon ship!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.73,0:21:47.88,Default,,0,0,0,,All crew have abandoned{/left} the ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.70,0:21:51.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You put up a good fight,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.56,0:21:54.46,Default,,0,0,0,,a brave knight, and a champion of the British Empire.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.14,0:21:58.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain! Let's hurry to get on the boats! {no clue what's the last word}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.36,0:22:01.47,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I'm good enough here. {no clue what he means by genki, was "No, I'm fine." in HA}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.47,0:22:02.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Chief!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.27,0:22:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.07,0:22:04.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.87,0:22:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.18,0:22:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir!! {hope its kakka}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.18,0:22:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.82,0:22:24.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Prince of Wales is sinking!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.87,0:22:25.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.89,0:22:27.53,Default,,0,0,0,,we've no fuel for the way back! {/to return}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.53,0:22:29.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Report the results of the battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.21,0:22:38.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Watch out!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.11,0:22:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Think they're out of bullets? {no clue what's this tennai, believibng HA; also he says that to ask "why didn't the plane shoot us in the water"}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.68,0:22:45.40,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it was Bushido!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.09,0:22:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,We did it?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.53,0:22:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.33,0:22:56.02,Default,,0,0,0,,An airplane sunk an unsinkable battleship.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.19,0:22:59.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The fall of Singapore is now but a matter of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.60,0:23:18.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The next day, a Japanese plane flew over to the sinking site \Nof Prince of Wales and Repulse.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.58,0:23:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,There, it dropped two wreathes.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.80,0:23:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,In the High Seas Naval Battle for Malaya,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.78,0:23:29.43,Default,,0,0,0,,both the Japanese and British forces{actually "fleets" but we saw that the jap fleet never made it there} fought splendidly, \Nimpressing the enemy with their majestic performance. {lit: was a beautiful and magnificent fighting}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.21,0:23:34.20,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the wreathes was intended \Nfor the British soldiers.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.20,0:23:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And the other one was dedicated \Nto the fallen Japanese soldiers.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.75,0:23:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The wreathes symbolized the respect{added} for those who keep on \Nfighting despite all odds, determined to fulfill their duty. {lit: devoted/dedicated to that mentality}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.82,0:23:47.13,Default,,0,0,0,,However, albeit not yet fully realizing it,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.13,0:23:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,inadvertently, with those wreathes, \Nthe Japanese Navy ushered in the age of aircraft. {/what the Japanese Navy really symbolized with those wreathes was the arrival of the aircraft era.}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.59,0:23:56.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And before long, that short-sightedness{/imperceptiveness - I know this word doesn't exist but I can't think of a better one} \Nwould spell a major disaster for themselves. {I think he means "by not realizing it, they started walking on a way to a major defeat"}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.93,0:24:07.76,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fade(100,0)}The Pacific War taught us the preciousness of peace.\NBut also instilled numerous lessons on how to live.{太平洋戦争はわれわれに平和の尊さを教えたがまた生きるための教訓を数多くのこしている}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.90,0:24:12.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Next time, in the Southern Pacific, \Nthe Coral Sea would serve as a backdrop. {/stage}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.14,0:24:14.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The Japanese plan to capture Port Moresby
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.97,0:24:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,will soon bring about the first ever in the world's \Nnaval warfare history carrier-on-carrier battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.75,0:24:22.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Zeros and Grummans would come together \Nin a spectacular dogfight. {actually "aerial battle"}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.73,0:24:25.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, amidst a terrible squall,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.46,0:24:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,looking for a prime chance of scoring a victory, {/most favorable} {no clue what's this otte, might be "to owe (a debt of gratitude to); to be indebted to" but idc bc jikai}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.00,0:24:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,both the Japanese and American task forces \Nwould apply all of their wisdom in the fight{added}. {not sure what's megurasu - to think over; to work out; to consider; to ponder; to devise; to plan - here}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.49,0:24:38.04,Sign,,0,0,0,,Episode 8 \N{Naval }Battle of the Coral Sea {珊瑚海海戦}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.24,0:24:37.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Next week's decision: \NBattle of the Coral Sea. Don't miss it.
